      • onPropertyChange

        public void onPropertyChange(com.skype.api.Conversation obj,
                    com.skype.api.Conversation.Property prop,
                    int value,
                    String svalue)
        Description copied from class: Net4CareListeners
        ConversationListener Override: Tutorial Handler - Conversation "Live Status".

        If it's not a "live status" change, ignore it. Otherwise:
        • display changes to our live status
        • handle answering calls for us
        Tutorial 6/7 - Looks for:
        • RINGING_FOR_ME so we can pick up the call
        • IM_LIVE to indicate that a call is in progress
        • RECENTLY_LIVE/NONE to indicate that a call has ended
        Specified by:
        onPropertyChange in interface com.skype.api.ConversationListener
        Overrides:
        onPropertyChange in class Net4CareListeners
        Parameters:
        obj - The affected Conversation.
        prop - The Conversation property that triggered this event.
        value - Ignored.

      • doPickUpCall

        public boolean doPickUpCall()
        Description copied from class: Net4CareListeners
        Business logic for answering a call (Tutorial_5 - Find conversation to join).

        Since this method is invoked from the Conversation event handler Net4CareListeners.onPropertyChange(com.skype.api.Conversation, com.skype.api.Conversation.Property, int, String), it's most convenient to place it here in the JavaTutorialListeners class.
        Overrides:
        doPickUpCall in class Net4CareListeners
        Returns:
        • true: call picked up
        • false: no call to pick up/call not answered/error
